title: Poll: Will the Mets win the series against the Cubs? - NJ.com
text:
The New York Mets bumped off the Dodgers in a taut 3-2 victory in Game 5 of the Division Series Thursday night to advance to the National League Championship Series against the Chicago Cubs, which begins tonight. 
Good-bye Kershaw and Greinke, hello Arrieta and Lester. 
Although both teams have long been tagged as lovable losers - the Mets haven't won the championship since 1986, the Cubs since 1908 - they both enter this series with great young hurlers and packing a punch. 
Since the All-Star break, Cubs rookie Kyle Schwarber has hit 15 home runs with a .352 on-base percentage. Since he was moved from shortstop to second base, Cubby Starlin Castro has led baseball with a .426 September batting average. And Cub starter Jake Arrieta has been lights out, notching a .99 ERA since the start of July. 
The Dodgers won all seven contests against the Amazins this season. 
But all those games games were played between May 11 and July 2. 
As noted by ESPN , David Wright missed the entire season series because he was rehabbing a back injury. Travis d'Arnaud was on the shelf. Michael Conforto and Steven Matz had yet to be promoted from the minors. And Yoenis Cespedes, Kelly Johnson, Tyler Clippard and Addison Reed had not yet been acquired in four separate trades.
